			<div class="content" id="post-content-3781490">
									

<p>As Aceofmoxes said, it's one of the lines from the song Hotel California. Additionally, <em>all</em> of this story's chapter titles are going to be lyrics from that song, and the overall story title <em>Faraway Voices</em> is a reference to the line &quot;and still those voices are calling from far away&quot; as well. It's all fitting to the story, which will become more and more apparent (I hope!) as events unfold.</p>
<p>More specifically, I chose &quot;Programmed to Receive&quot; for this chapter because that's exactly what has been done with Site-3408: Its automated systems have been literally programmed to receive and contain anomalies. In a more metaphorical sense, it also refers to Janice's arrival at the site.</p>

							</div>

								
					
